summaries.short: Devon plays the vixen at dinner with Richie, Hannibal and Cece; Kip faces a band dilemma.
summaries.full: Richie visits a close relative in order to leverage a favor to his advantage. Devon agrees to join Richie for dinner with Hannibal and Cece, playing up the vixen role to keep one of her husband's biggest clients signed. Kip faces a tough dilemma. Richie tries to recruit Andrea Zito, a former employee and flame. Clark gets a new job after an emotional meeting with Julie.

summaries.short: Richie falls in a deeper well of depravity as Devon seeks refuge with old friends at the Chelsea Hotel.
summaries.full: Devon seeks refuge at the Chelsea Hotel with Ingrid, a friend from her Warhol days. Meanwhile, Richie falls into a deeper well of drugs and depravity, enabled by Ingrid's nihilistic boyfriend Ernst. Andrea Zito rejoins American Century and immediately outlines her plans to revive the label. Kip follows an unlikely path towards recruiting a new lead guitarist for the Nasty Bits.

summaries.short: Richie charms a funk superstar; Skip looks to unload a shipment of Donny Osmond LPs.
summaries.full: Richie charms a funk superstar; Skip looks to unload a shipment of Donny Osmond LPs. Zak and Scott ruminate on their futures in the aftermath of the lost deal with German Polygram. On the verge of signing with American Century, Kip and the Nasty Bits enlist a new manager to work out a favorable deal with Richie.

summaries.short: On a hunch, Richie and Zak travel to Las Vegas in hopes of persuading Elvis Presley to switch labels.
summaries.full: Looking to raise cash for his label, a newly sober Richie flies to LA with Zak, hoping to sell the company jet to a rival record exec, Lou Meshejian. Later, Richie and Zak head to Las Vegas in hopes of somehow convincing Elvis Presley and his manager to sign with American Century. The detour includes a steamy encounter in which Zak's fantasies come true, at a price.

summaries.short: Richie trims the American Century roster; Devon tries her hand at fundraising in the suburbs.
summaries.full: At a record producers' banquet honoring Maury Gold, Richie is embarrassed when the emcee, rival record exec Jackie Jervis, makes a joke about the failed German Polygram deal. Later, Maury and mob cohort Corrado Galasso pay a visit to American Century to probe a detective's recent inquiry, and Joe Corso drops by to pitch Richie a demo by his banquet date, Nora.

summaries.short: A desperate Richie approaches Galasso about a loan; Kip gets a crash course in the blues from Lester.
summaries.full: A desperate Richie approaches Maury about doing a deal with Galasso. Devon and Ingrid make the scene at Max's Kansas City, where Devon impresses photographer Billy McVicar. Tasked by Richie to come up with a new song, Kip and the Nasty Bits get a crash course in the blues from Lester. Andrea fires a longtime American Century employee, angering Richie.

summaries.short: Terence Winter, Mick Jagger and Martin Scorsese discuss how the new HBO series 'Vinyl' depicts the birth of hip hop in 1970s New York.
summaries.full: Terence Winter, Mick Jagger and Martin Scorsese, the executive producers of the new HBO series 'Vinyl,' discuss how the show depicts the birth of hip hop and the evolution of DJing in 1970s New York.

summaries.short: Cultural innovators from the '70s discuss street art, the origins of hip hop, modeling and art with their contemporaries of today.
summaries.full: Cultural innovators from the '70s are paired with present-day influencers for an immersive conversation about street art, fashion, hip-hop, style and artistry that highlight what has changed in NYC over that time. Interviews include models Pat and Anna Cleveland, Kool DJ Red Alert, writer/editor Glenn O'Brien & music star Twin Shadow and graffiti artists Futura and Pixote.

summaries.short: Alice Cooper and Andrew W.K. talk about heavy metal, the early Detroit rock scene, their music, and more.

summaries.short: Richie delivers a bombshell that shocks American Century's would-be buyers--and blindsides his record-label partners, Zak and Skip.
summaries.full: With German Polygram executives in town to complete the deal for American Century, Richie delivers a bombshell that shocks the prospective buyers as well as his partners: Zak Yankovich, ACR's head of promotions, and Skip Fontaine, head of sales. When the dust settles, the Germans storm out of the ACR offices, leaving Richie to face the ire of Zak, Skip and Scott Levitt.
